# Tier T2 — code-prompts corpus for --eval-scope-matrix.
# 30 hand-graded EvalCase entries, every File / Symbol verified against
# the real gaviero-core source tree at authoring time. Distribution:
#   8 refactor / 7 bugfix / 8 feature / 7 explain
# Spread across 6 module roots: memory/, swarm/backend/, acp/,
#   context_planner/, repo_map/, write_gate.
#
# GoldRef variants used: File + Symbol only (corpus-content driven; no
# Memory / MemoryTag refs — those would require seeding rows first).
#
# Schema (T1.3 EvalCase, additive over the legacy shape):
#   id                  -- stable case id "cp-NNN"
#   query               -- user-style code prompt
#   scope               -- default scope hint ("repo" / "module" / "run")
#   tags                -- per-tag breakdown labels
#   kind                -- "refactor" | "bugfix" | "feature" | "explain"
#   gold_must           -- references that MUST surface (recall-binding)
#   gold_neutral        -- legitimate but not required
#   gold_forbid         -- must NOT surface (forbid_hit_rate)
#   graded              -- per-key relevance overrides (0..3)
#   expected_scope_path -- drives blast_leakage; matched against memory scope_path

